cu590_con | 1 | Some pages are worm-eaten, others are partly torn away.  Edges are worn and marginal ornaments are much damaged.  The paint used for outlining has eaten through the paper, causing the ornaments to break away and in some cases to fall out.  Some of the ornaments seem to have been deliberately cut out.  Nos. 18 and 23-25 came to the Oriental Institute in one loose cover measuring 30 x 41.9 cm, which is too small for No. 18 and too large for the others.  The red has oxidized and so now appears brown.  The script in the panels appears to be a very dull dark blue, but was likely painted over with white, as white traces can be seen in the sajdah ornament.
